{"id": 7838, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2020", "session": "20N", "subtopic": "1-2-the-mole-concept", "title": "20N.1.SL.TZ0.2", "topic_id": "1", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">What is the number of carbon atoms in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math> of ethanoic acid <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></math></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn></math><span class=\"fontstyle0\">?</span></p>\n<p>A.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>20</mn></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>23</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>23</mn></msup></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Approximately 57% of candidates could correctly apply Avogadro's number in calculating number of carbon atoms in 12 g of ethanoic acid. Many candidates did not identify that there were 2 carbon atoms per molecule.</p>\n</div>"}